      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLEETWOOD (5) has been freshened up since just missing in a busy finish over 1110m at Doomben six weeks ago. Gets in nicely on 55kgs and with blinkers applied off a six-week break expect him to be fired right up. SCAMPI (3) had been racing well before the eight-week let-up that preceded his game win in a comparable race to this at the Gold Coast three weeks back. Talented sprinter who thrives over this trip. Big chance to go back-to-back. Matthew Dunn has EMPEROR (6) on song this prep with two wins from as many runs, the latest over 1100m at Ipswich. Tackles better sprinters this time but with a soft run from the inside draw he is capable of featuring in the finish. GIVEMETHEBEATBOYS (1) is back from a six-month spell. Has raced at stakes level 16 times from 17 starts, so this is a soft assignment by his standards. Beaten 1.7 lengths by Mazu this time last year. Big market watch. EN POINTE (7) goes like the wind and can give some cheek first-up from a 16-week lay-off.",
